detailed.en:
"Hi boss, the current minimum withdrawal amount is RM30. Additionally, here are the guidelines for the betting categories:

â€¢ 4D (Tegak Sahaja): Includes prizes 4A (1st), 4B (2nd), 4C (3rd), 4D (Special), and 4E (Consolation).

â€¢ 3D: Based on the last three digits of the 4D number, with categories such as 3A (1st), 3B (2nd), 3C (3rd), 3D (Special, multiplied by 10), 3E (Consolation, multiplied by 10), and 3N covering all prizes.

â€¢ 2D: Based on the last two digits of the 4D number, with categories 2A (1st), 2B (2nd), 2C (3rd), 2D (Special, multiplied by 10), 2E (Consolation, multiplied by 10), and 2N covering all prizes.

For 3D and 2D, only the ending digits of the 4D number are used (e.g., if 4D = 1234, then 3D = 234 and 2D = 34)."
detailed.ms:
"Hi boss, jumlah minimum untuk withdrawal adalah RM30. Berikut juga panduan untuk kategori pertaruhan:

â€¢ 4D (Tegak Sahaja): Termasuk hadiah 4A (1st), 4B (2nd), 4C (3rd), 4D (Special) dan 4E (Consolation).

â€¢ 3D: Berdasarkan tiga digit terakhir nombor 4D, dengan kategori seperti 3A (1st), 3B (2nd), 3C (3rd), 3D (Special, X10), 3E (Consolation, X10) dan 3N merangkumi semua hadiah.

â€¢ 2D: Berdasarkan dua digit terakhir nombor 4D, dengan kategori 2A (1st), 2B (2nd), 2C (3rd), 2D (Special, X10), 2E (Consolation, X10) dan 2N merangkumi semua hadiah.

Untuk 3D dan 2D, hanya digit terakhir nombor 4D yang digunakan (contoh: jika 4D = 1234, maka 3D = 234 dan 2D = 34)."

languages.en: What do the abbreviations BT, BH, and RV mean in the context of betting?

detailed.en: In the context of 4D betting, the abbreviations mean the following: RV (Round Return â€“ Reverse Balik) refers to a number that is completely reversed (e.g., 1234 becomes 4321). BH (Pao Kepala â€“ First Digit Fixed) means the first digit remains the same while the others can change (e.g., 1223 can become 1232 or 1322). BT (Pao Ekor â€“ Last Digit Fixed) indicates that the last digit does not change while the others can be rearranged (e.g., 1223 can become 2123 or 2213). Additionally, IBOX is similar to BOX but with a fixed price of RM1, and the payout is divided according to the number of combinations. BOX is a bet that includes all possible combinations (the arrangement of digits can change).
detailed.ms: Dalam konteks pertaruhan 4D, singkatan ini bermaksud: RV (Round Return â€“ Reverse Balik) merujuk kepada nombor yang dibalik sepenuhnya (contohnya, 1234 menjadi 4321). BH (Pao Kepala â€“ Nombor Pertama Tak Bergerak) bermaksud digit pertama kekal sama manakala yang lain boleh berubah (contohnya, 1223 boleh jadi 1232 atau 1322). BT (Pao Ekor â€“ Nombor Akhir Tak Bergerak) menunjukkan bahawa digit terakhir tidak berubah manakala yang lain boleh disusun semula (contohnya, 1223 boleh jadi 2123 atau 2213). Selain itu, IBOX adalah sama seperti BOX tetapi dengan harga tetap RM1, dan pembayaran dibahagikan mengikut bilangan kombinasi. BOX adalah pertaruhan yang merangkumi semua kemungkinan kombinasi (susunan digit boleh berubah).

languages.en: What should I do if the system is slow and I need to upload a receipt?
languages.ms: Apa yang perlu saya buat jika sistem lambat dan saya perlu muat naik resit?

detailed.en: If the system is slow, please wait a moment for your receipt to be processed. If it takes more than 10 minutes, contact us for further assistance. If you have already uploaded the receipt, ensure the correct amount is entered and wait for the system to process it within 3 to 10 minutes. If it still does not appear, you can send the receipt via live chat for further checking. If you mistakenly selected the wrong bank while uploading the receipt, wait for the system to reject it before uploading again with the correct bank. Do not upload the same receipt twice before it is rejected to avoid issues in the top-up process.
